pollutant /pəˈluːtənt/

(pollutants) 

1. N-VAR Pollutants are substances that pollute the environment, especially gases from vehicles and poisonous chemicals produced as waste by industrial processes. 污染物 (尤指车辆尾气和化学工业废料) 

例： Industrial pollutants are responsible for a sizable proportion of all cancers. 工业污染物会引发多种癌症。

